      "followed_by_phoneme": [
        "dʒa",
        "dʒ"
      ],
      "notes": "Tamil gemination, first half. A doubled consonant letter (C + virama + C) is a phonetically LONG consonant, transcribed with the length mark (Keane 2004: 111-116, 'Tamil', Journal of the IPA 34(1); Krishnamurti 2003: ch. 4). The cluster's first member — the vowel-less consonant — carries the length: புத்தகம் [put̪ːaɡam], அக்கா [akːaː]. The second half is stripped to its bare vowel by TA_GEM2_*, so the pair rewrites C+C+V to Cː+V. A geminate is ALWAYS voiceless, which is why the geminate rules are ordered before the voicing rules: first match wins."
    },
