      "notes": "Tamil gemination, second half (see TA_GEM1_*): the second member of a geminate contributes only its vowel, the consonant itself having been absorbed into the length mark on the first member (Keane 2004: 111-116). Firing before the voicing rules is what keeps a geminate voiceless — பக்கம் [pakːam], never *[paɡam] (Keane 2004: 113: voicing is blocked in geminates)."
