      "notes": "Voicing guard. Tamil has NO phonemic voicing contrast in stops: voicing is positional (Keane 2004: 111-116; Krishnamurti 2003: 4.2; Wikipedia, 'Tamil phonology'). A stop is VOICELESS word-initially and when it follows another vowel-less obstruent or liquid (i.e. inside a cluster that is not nasal+stop): பார்ப்பு, கற்க. This identity rewrite fires first in exactly that context and — first match wins — blocks TA_VOICE_*. Nasals are deliberately absent from the list: a stop AFTER a nasal is voiced (TA_VOICE_*), தங்கம் [t̪aŋɡam]."
